    // x_0 = x-1, k_0 = k.
    // s[x_0] = s[x_0+k_0] = s[x_0+2k_0]
    // The range for this triplet is [x_0, x_0+2k_0].
    // The problem states l <= x < x+2k <= r.
    // So for a triplet (x_0, k_0), any (l, r) such that l-1 <= x_0 and x_0+2k_0 <= r-1 will be "good".
    // We are interested in the smallest r-1 that makes (l, r) good for a given l-1.
    // This means we are interested in x_0+2k_0.
