    // A '01' pattern at index i means a[i]=0, a[i+1]=1
    // A '10' pattern at index i means a[i]=1, a[i+1]=0
    // These are the "boundaries" between blocks of identical numbers.
    // The median smoothing operation effectively shrinks these boundaries.
